      },
      "date": "2012-08-31 06:22:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, approved\n\nMinh, in the future it makes more sense to base the \"real\" patch directly on master, and then specify:\n\n Test-Parameters: envparameter=USE_OFD=yes\n\nfor each patch instead of making this patch depend on another patch that will not be landed (or at least not for a while until OFD testing is more solid). That will ensure that the code is being tested, and the patch can more easiy be landed to master. It is ossible to land this patch directly without the first one, but it can become more complex if many patches are involved.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6e7131a8c17381aa1490d8a213295a4d16edd699",
      "author": {
